{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-tsx","path":"/arduino-tone/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Arduino <code class=\"language-text\">tone()</code> function</h1>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.arduino.cc/reference/en/language/functions/advanced-io/tone/\"><strong>Arduino <code class=\"language-text\">tone()</code> function</strong></a> generates a square wave of the specified frequency on a pin, which can be used to emit a tone.</p>\n<h2>Use <code class=\"language-text\">tone()</code> to Play a Melody</h2>\n<p>The following code was adapted from the <a href=\"https://www.arduino.cc/en/Tutorial/BuiltInExamples/toneMelody\">Play a Melody using the tone() function</a> Built-In Example tutorial.</p>\n<iframe src=https://create.arduino.cc/editor/jamestharpe/3ef73b15-330f-4a70-ab8f-b24697ef66d5/preview?F=pitches.h?embed style=\"height:510px;width:100%;margin:10px 0\" frameborder=0></iframe>","fields":{"slug":"/arduino-tone/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Arduino tone() Function","tags":["arduino-programming"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/arduino-tone/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2270328656","3794076007","80858887"]}